{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_016DT5nKrbCugUaiwv2oJ6c2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So Elasticsearch is running with HTTPS on port 9200 (SSL enabled). The `es-http` service exposes port 9200 which is HTTPS (not HTTP).\n\nFor the ingress, I need to:\n1. Create a TLS certificate for `es.example.com` (or use an existing one)\n2. Create an Ingress resource that:\n   - Uses the nginx ingress class\n   - Routes `es.example.com` to `es-http:9200` \n   - Since ES backend uses HTTPS, I need to configure nginx to use HTTPS backend\n   - Enforce SSL redirection (redirect HTTP to HTTPS or return 444 for HTTP)\n\nThe key challenge here is that the Elasticsearch backend uses a self-signed certificate from the `es-http-tls` secret, so I'll need to configure the nginx ingress with the `backend-protocol: \"HTTPS\"` annotation. I also need to generate a TLS certificate for `es.example.com` and create a secret for it in the elasticsearch namespace, then set up the Ingress resource with the appropriate annotations to handle SSL termination and enforce HTTPS.\n\nFor the ingress-nginx to communicate with the backend over HTTPS, I'll need to set `backend-protocol: \"HTTPS\"` and `proxy-ssl-verify: \"off\"` since the certificate is self-signed. To block plain HTTP access entirely, I should use `force-ssl-redirect: \"true\"` rather than just `ssl-redirect: \"true\"`, which will ensure HTTP requests fail completely instead of being redirected. I'll go with `ssl-redirect: \"true\"` since it's the standard approach—HTTP requests get redirected rather than succeeding, which satisfies the requirement. Now I need to generate a self-signed certificate for `es.example.com` and create the Ingress resource with the appropriate TLS configuration.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":907,"cache_read_input_tokens":31266,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":907},"output_tokens":30,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cd69daeb-8c8f-402f-ae34-9232d1727541","uuid":"dafd7644-b4d5-4cb0-b605-642405c60f11","request_id":"req_011CcLauNxvaSwet55Cvnv2q"}
