{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KXwbaSJCmZFqJUxQ5h6uyn","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is working correctly. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Setup complete:**\n\n1. **TLS certificate** — Generated a self-signed cert for `es.example.com` and stored it as secret `es-ingress-tls` in the `elasticsearch` namespace.\n\n2. **Ingress resource** (`elasticsearch-ingress`) created with:\n   - `ingressClassName: nginx` — uses the nginx ingress class\n   - `backend-protocol: HTTPS` — because Elasticsearch itself runs HTTPS (xpack.security.http.ssl enabled)\n   - `proxy-ssl-verify: off` — skips verification of the ES self-signed backend cert\n   - `ssl-redirect: true` + `force-ssl-redirect: true` — plain HTTP returns `308 Permanent Redirect` and never succeeds\n   - TLS termination using the `es-ingress-tls` secret for `es.example.com`\n\n3. **Cluster health restored** — The ES pods had a stale `ELASTIC_PASSWORD` env var (old value from before a password rotation). Restarted the StatefulSet so pods picked up the current secret value; all 3 pods are now `1/1 Ready` and the cluster is `green`.\n\n**Verification results:**\n- `HTTPS` → `200 OK` with valid credentials (cluster health: green)\n- `HTTPS` → `401` without credentials (ES auth wall, ingress routing works)\n- `HTTP` → `308 Permanent Redirect` — plain HTTP does not succeed"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":791,"cache_read_input_tokens":47221,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":791},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cd69daeb-8c8f-402f-ae34-9232d1727541","uuid":"4c00aeb3-24b3-4e50-ad8b-8bb023541adc","request_id":"req_011CcLbgeushs8x9UgnGCq2C"}
